{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Related to: <b> λοιπός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> (λείπω) <b>remaining over</b>, not in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, frequently from 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus and 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus downwards; λ. βίοτος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.97; λ.εὐχαί [prev. work] 4.15; λ.γένος [prev. work] 2.15 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also λοιποί <b>descendants</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “I.” 4(3).39: in Prose the _Article_ is commonly added, and ὁ λ.\">Refs</a>] either agrees with the Noun or takes a dependent genitive, αἱ λ. τῶν νεῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.72 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν λοιπὴν (i.e. ὁδὸν) πορευσόμεθα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.46; τὸ λ. τῆς ἡμέρας [prev. work] 16, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> λοιπόν [ἐστι] with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>it remains</b> to show, etc., ἀποδεικνύναι, διελέσθαι, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Smp.” 4.1, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 466d, etc.: also with _Article_, τὸ λ. ἤδη ἡμῖν ἐστι σκέψασθαι, πότερον\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>what remains</b> for us is to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 444e; διανομὴ τοίνυν τὸ λ. σοι [prev. work] 535a: without \">Refs</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, ὃ δὲ λ. <b>quod superest</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1571 (Lyric poetry); ὅ τι λ. πόνων [prev. author] “Pr.” 684; τὸ εὐπρεπείας πέρι.. λοιπόν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 274b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> frequently of Time, ὁ λ. χρόνος <b>the future</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.67; πρὸς τὸν λοιπὸν τοῦ χρόνου 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 15.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν λ. χρόνον <b>for the future</b